<BaseLayout title="About Omegon Armory | Omegon Armory" description="What Omegon Armory publishes and how its artifacts are distributed.">
  <article class="docs-page">
    <p class="eyebrow">About</p>
    <h1>Omegon Armory is an artifact registry for agent ecosystems.</h1>

    <p>
      Armory publishes reviewed agent ecosystem packages for Omegon: skills, personas, tones,
      profiles, catalog agents, and extensions. The site is intentionally static. The generated
      catalog API and package pages are derived from repository manifests.
    </p>

    <h2>Distribution surfaces</h2>
    <p>
      Skills, personas, tones, profiles, and catalog agents are packaged as signed OCI artifacts.
      Extensions are resolved by name through the Omegon extension registry and installed from
      upstream release metadata.
    </p>

    <h2>Compatibility posture</h2>
    <p>
      Omegon is the full-fidelity runtime. Other agent hosts can still consume many packages in
      degraded form: instruction packs, role prompts, dependency manifests, agent blueprints, or
      external tool references. Each generated catalog item declares its native and degraded
      compatibility metadata.
    </p>

    <h2>Security posture</h2>
    <p>
      Public Armory payloads are treated as world-readable and mirrorable. Publication gates lint
      package payloads for obvious secrets, private topology, private hostnames, private IPs, and
      operational memory facts before release.
    </p>

